## Enforcing Minimum Scores

In automated pipelines and CI you often want to *fail the run* when a dimension slips below an
acceptable level. Call [`assert_dimension_scores()`](`pointblank.Validate.assert_dimension_scores`)
with per-dimension minimums; it raises an `AssertionError` if any dimension is below its minimum
(here, uniqueness is `80%`):

::: {#479fb915 .cell execution_count=9}
``` {.python .cell-code}
try:
    validation.assert_dimension_scores(thresholds={"uniqueness": 95})
except AssertionError as e:
    print(e)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Dimension health score(s) below the required minimum: uniqueness (80% < 95%)
```
:::
:::


Dimensions present in the thresholds but absent from the validation are ignored, and a call where
every dimension meets its minimum simply returns without raising. You can also set the minimums
globally with `config(dimension_thresholds=...)`, and then call the method without arguments:

::: {#32fc327f .cell execution_count=10}
``` {.python .cell-code}
pb.config(dimension_thresholds={"completeness": 95})

try:
    validation.assert_dimension_scores()
except AssertionError as e:
    print(e)

pb.config()  # reset back to defaults
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Dimension health score(s) below the required minimum: completeness (90% < 95%)
```
:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=10}
